The article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by Donald J. Trump on September 30, 2017. The memorandum discusses the Presidential Determination with respect to the Child Soldiers Prevention Act of 2008. It states that the President has determined it is in the national interest of the United States to waive the application of the prohibition in section 404(a) of the Act with respect to Mali, Nigeria, the Democratic Republic of the Congo, Somalia, and South Sudan. The waivers are to allow for the provision of various types of assistance and support, such as Peacekeeping Operations assistance and International Military Education and Training assistance. The memorandum directs the submission of this determination to Congress and publication in the Federal Register.